    {
      "id": "81",
      "name": "Lore",
      "components": [
        {
          "component_id": "customize",
          "data": {
            "data": {
              "parsed_content": [
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Archon War",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Several thousand years ago, the Heavenly Principles declared war among the gods for the divine thrones, and the lands of Liyue became a battlefield. Rex Lapis and the Adepti of the South fought against the Adepti of the North and other gods. Countless gods, Adepti, and Yakshas died in this war. Among the victims were the youngest of the Yaksha, Pervases, to whom Rex Lapis personally bestowed a name, and the Goddess of Dust, Guizhong, whose power the Yakshas sealed away to prevent its release. There was no place where the souls of the dead could return.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/90f7b599b4d7f65c3edf3844d9cf3f04_5990369071033377616.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In one of the battles, Rex Lapis defeated a god that the young Yaksha, one of the Adepti, served. He was forced to do unimaginably terrible things, he ruined many lives, crushed many hopes, and devoured the dreams of the victims he killed. As much as it pained him to do this, he was helpless to resist. When Morax defeated the Yaksha's master, he freed him and gave him the name Xiao to protect him:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"In the fables of another land, the name Xiao is that of a spirit who encountered great suffering and hardship. He endured much suffering, as you have. Use this name from now on.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In gratitude for the kindness of Rex Lapis,",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "took on the protection of Liyue for the coming millennia. Since all his gentleness and innocence had been lost during his service to the evil deity, and only the burden of his sins and the ability to kill remained, Xiao could only help the people of Liyue in battle.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/07c5b1b79ed283b8ce32f56522a1dbae_6458912599486681398.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "3,700 years ago, Morax defeated the other gods of Liyue and founded Liyue Harbor with the Adepti. The Adepti made a pact with Rex Lapis and swore to protect the people of Liyue. Although Morax defeated all the gods and buried them under the mountain cliffs, they are immortal. Their consciousness may diminish, but their power and hatred will always remain and spread like poison, relentlessly stirring up chaos for the world and its inhabitants. The gods who returned to the cycle of elements did not give up but returned in the form of demons. Tormented by anger, they gave rise to a miasma, which in turn engendered all manner of plagues, monsters, and other perverse evils. They starved the earth and churned the waters, and wrought devastation on the people. To purge the demons, Rex Lapis summoned the Yakshas. The Yakshas, fierce and warlike, illuminated beasts of Liyue, were ready to do anything to protect the lands. In battle with demons, they wore masks that terrified the demons, hiding the part of themselves that made them human. The Yakshas swore to restore order and deal with evil:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Restore order through slaughter, purge evil through battle. To this, we dedicate our lives.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Five of the many were the strongest: Marshal Vritras Bosacius, General Musatas Indarias, General Chizapus Bonanus, General Kapisas Menogias, and the Golden-Winged King Alatus. Together with the Archon, they banished plagues, defeated demons, and became known unto mortals as \"The Yakshas.\" They knew that the war they fight can never be won, and would never come to an end. It is also an invisible war that no one will ever witness or thank them for.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/548e5247deab8a521e2c9f8d040c062f_2241455296625011163.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "The Yakshas mercilessly killed countless incarnations of the vengeful remains of the gods, but in doing so, their souls were fractured. Eventually, these fragments of their hatred were able to taint the Yakshas' souls, condemning them to terrible suffering from the karmic debt. Some descended into a blind rage of a kind that cannot be put into words or were driven by fear to equally indescribable madness. Some turned on and destroyed each other and some were lost to delusions of the mind. After a thousand years of scourges, three of the five were slain.",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/fd7d2c27514b9c50f2f6057c5d987cc3_7052495050928265229.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Menogias and Bonanus turned on each other, and Bonanus pierced her brother with a spear. Indarias succumbed to the influence of the karmic debt and died. The fourth Yaksha, Bosacius, went mad and disappeared, leaving his wealth sealed by the Adeptal arts, and only Alatus remained alive. The terrible deeds committed over long millennia began to eat away at the Golden-Winged King from within. He lost his kin, friends, and allies, faced the impossibility of redemption, burnt in everlasting anger, and knew no respite. He turned against his past grievances but received neither retribution nor relief, and his reward was only an emptiness in his heart that eternity could not fill. One day most of Xiao's strength was spent fighting from dusk till dawn, with him emerging victorious by a mere hair. Long exhausted, Conqueror of Demons felt the divine hatred that tainted his body take effect. Limitless hate flooded his senses, and he fell to the ground in agony. But it was also at that moment that the pain vanished without warning. This was not by Xiao's own strength, for he had been rescued by the sound of a flute of the Anemo Archon, Barbatos. The clear, lovely sound of the flute came over the mountains and rivers, carried on the wind to where he lay. It protected Alatus, massaging his wild senses, and giving him a moment's peace. And although the Conqueror of Demons was alone his entire life, there were still people in the world ready to protect him.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
