                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/book/Verses of Equilibrium_icon.png",
                      "menu_id": 12,
                      "name": "Песни равновесия",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Cataclysm",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/9a723eb62826da5b39b435eec28c8297_1287605558445924247.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "500 years ago, a cataclysm occurred in Khaenri'ah, and the Abyss poured into this world. The Chasm, where ancient evil had long been hiding, became the center of battles with the monsters of the Abyss. The Milleliths were tasked with evacuating the locals and miners, and some soldiers remained at the Chasm to cover the retreat. The four-armed Yaksha, Bosacius, came to their aid. With a sword in his hands, he entered the Chasm to put an end to the suffering of people. Purple bale-fire shone in his eyes, and people said that the Yaksha defended the Chasm not to fulfill the order of Rex Lapis, but to atone for eternal sins, to gain forgiveness for the cowardice and weakness he once showed. Be that as it may, the Yaksha descended into the mines with the Milleliths. In the course of fighting side-by-side with the Yaksha, these mortal soldiers could not escape being contaminated by karma, or harmed during the slaughtering. To avoid being consumed by the darkness of constant killing, the Millelith soldiers used a timepiece to silently mark the passage of time during each battle. They fixed a unified marching pace and schedule so that one squadron of mortal soldiers would take the battlefield as the one before they retreated. This cycle of advance and retreat continued all the way to the depths of the Chasm, where the Yaksha and valiant soldiers both fell.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/90ec28a7bc8d4e51d7db9d334bd6a40d_2423246889581117515.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Together with one of the mortals, Boyan, Bosacius descended into the subspace of the Chasm, where time and space were distorted. It used the weaknesses and fears of people and showed them illusions to lure them into a trap. Because of karma, the Yaksha forgot himself, his brothers and sisters, and why he came to the Chasm. At the cost of their lives, Boyan and Bosacius were able to seal the subspace with the Fantastic Compass — an artifact capable of changing space and sealing monsters. Before dying, the four-armed Yaksha's mind cleared, and he remembered his friends. Bosacius remained trapped in the Chasm, and Alatus later encountered his phantom manifestation in this subspace when he arrived in the mines to search for his missing brother. To escape the subspace and save the people, Xiao was ready to sacrifice himself but he was saved by Rex Lapis.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
