                      "amount": 0,
                      "display_style": "card",
                      "ep_id": 2097,
                      "icon_url": "https://bbs.hoyolab.com/hoyowiki/picture/reliquary/Vermillion Hereafter/flower_of_life_icon.png",
                      "menu_id": 5,
                      "name": "Киноварное загробье",
                      "type": "custom_entry"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "alignment": "center",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 255, 255)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Legacy",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "level": 1,
                  "type": "heading"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/d62233f03601be3f1482da55fc406cc0_7401207558544153494.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "During a bygone war, the people of Liyue illuminated the night sky with lanterns to serve as a reminder of the way home to their warriors and to never lose sight of themselves. Lantern Rite is an annual festivity to honor these heroes. On this day, the people pray for prosperity to descend upon them and for troubles to go away. At night, the city's residents launch many sky lanterns and one large moon lantern into the sky. Only in springtime, during the offering of lanterns at night, might the people see the glow at Guyun and declare:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Behold, the Vigilant Yaksha ends the dominion of daemons!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "Or they might hear the sound of a flute amongst the marsh reeds, but find none who play the flute, and thus declare:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Hark, the yaksha calls to summon his old friends to their homeland.\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/dfcd3f2011935d6162fe5cd362960c47_4538355187157167310.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In memory of the Yaksha’s deeds, people erected statues of them. It was believed that the mighty Yakshas were doomed to wander the land in a state of unending suffering. To comfort the Yakshas, they were offered food and sung holy chants. All this would appease the Yaksha and give them strength to continue defending the peace. Today, huge statues of the Yakshas defeating evil spirits still stand in Liyue, but their faces have long since deteriorated beyond recognition. In the mortal world, almost nothing is known about the Yakshas, because they are not popular deities that bring wealth and protection, and not mystical sages to whom pilgrims flock in search of divine wisdom. No one would think of thanking Xiao, for they would be terrified of his divine power. The sight of Xiao, even far off in the distance, was intimidating enough to send people instantly running for their lives. However, the Qixing, which governs Liyue, assigned one of their secret agents to support the Conqueror of Demons in subduing demons. That secret agent runs a front organization called the Wangshu Inn. Occasionally, Xiao stops by the inn for a bowl of Almond Tofu, which reminds him of the dreams he used to devour.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "left",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/8b671dfbeb1e2ed7a75088c60db5de9b_3776640753422333091.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "One day, a mortal decided to pretend to be a Yaksha and call himself Starsnatcher, gathering followers. He gave people medicine, accompanied merchants, and helped the brokenhearted in exchange for donations. Using the Sigil of Permission, he drove away demons but did not kill them, so they gradually gathered in one place, threatening people with danger. After learning about the fraud, the Conqueror of Demons used an Adeptal art named Dream Trawler to summon the soul of Starsnatcher. The ritual consists of four parts: offering incense, meditation, incantation, and loosing an arrow. To offer incense, one needs to place the incense into the censer with reverence for Rex Lapis in their hearts. Meditation is to empty people of trivial thoughts and to focus on the target of the art we are performing. Then, people shall recite the incantation in a loud voice:",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "italic"
                      ],
                      "text": "\"Devayaksha, Bring Forth Sin!\"",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ", and finally — loose an arrow toward each of the Yaksha statues to enlist their authority for the contract. When the soul of the false Adeptus was summoned, he swore to Alatus to renounce evil, live according to his conscience, and not defame the name of the Adepti.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "alignment": "right",
                      "type": "custom_image",
                      "url": "https://act-upload.hoyoverse.com/event-ugc-hoyowiki/2024/12/22/237301566/4034daf7d995376ffadd9d0bc70d02cd_4298174480460191849.png"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "In honor of the memory of the Yaksha Pervases, a temple was built, but over time, people stopped coming there, and it collapsed. Using the special Adeptal art Mortal Lingering, the Seven-Star Lamps, and the censer, the deceased Yaksha was able to incarnate in the world as an illusion on the day of his death to look at modern Liyue. Wang Ping'an, who renounced the name of Starsnatcher and decided to atone for his sins, rebuilt Pervases’s temple. Sometimes, Xiao comes to this temple to remember his dead brothers and sisters and to bring Pervases the Grilled Tiger Fish he loved.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "styles": [
                        "bold",
                        "color:rgb(255, 215, 128)"
                      ],
                      "text": "Related Entries:",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                },
                {
